S3PBT02/S3PBT03 Alpha runtime lifecycle, shutdown, and fault-injection evidence
date: 2026-06-24
project: Alpha
acceptance: ACC-S3PBT02
scope:
- AutoPaperAgentRuntime stop/cancel lifecycle truthfulness.
- Dashboard start/stop PID file cleanup.
- Startup failure cleanup for the dashboard process started by the script.
- LF enforcement for Alpha shell scripts so bash syntax validation is stable on Windows worktrees.

commands:
- python -B -m py_compile Alpha\backend\app\services\agent_runtime.py Alpha\tests\test_agent_runtime.py Alpha\tests\test_lifecycle_scripts.py
  result: PASS
  observed: Python syntax/import bytecode compilation completed with exit 0.
- /bin/bash -n Alpha/scripts/start_alpha_dashboard.sh
  result: PASS
  observed: start script parses after Alpha/scripts/*.sh LF enforcement.
- /bin/bash -n Alpha/scripts/stop_alpha_dashboard.sh
  result: PASS
  observed: stop script parses after Alpha/scripts/*.sh LF enforcement.
- set PYTHONPATH=Alpha && python -B C:\Users\linze\Documents\Codex\2026-06-23\xian\work\s3pbt02_alpha_lifecycle_smoke.py
  result: PASS
  observed: runtime lifecycle smoke passed graceful drain, stop_timeout truthfulness, no second cycle after stopped, PID atomic write assertions, TERM-to-KILL escalation assertions, and PID preservation assertions.
- python -B -m pytest Alpha\tests -k "runtime or lifecycle" -q
  result: NOT_RUN_LOCAL_TOOL_UNAVAILABLE
  observed: local Python reports No module named pytest.

implemented_controls:
- AutoPaperAgentRuntime.stop sets enabled=false, marks stopping, signals the stop event, and waits for the current task without asyncio.wait_for cancellation.
- A drained current cycle can complete before stop returns stopped; no second cycle is scheduled after stop_event is set.
- If the current cycle does not drain before the timeout, stop returns status=stop_timeout with task_running=true and stopping=true instead of claiming stopped.
- Snapshot now exposes stopping, last_stopped_at, and stop_timeout_count for owner-visible runtime truth.
- start_alpha_dashboard.sh validates stale or invalid PID files, archives them, writes PID files through a temp file plus mv, and cleans up failed startup by TERM then KILL before deleting the PID file.
- stop_alpha_dashboard.sh validates PID file contents, archives stale invalid/inactive PID files, waits after TERM, escalates to KILL, and preserves the PID file if the process remains active.
- .gitattributes pins Alpha/scripts/*.sh to LF so shell scripts do not regress to CRLF under core.autocrlf=true.

not_claimed:
- S3PBT02 does not prove POSIX live process termination against a real uvicorn process in this Windows workspace.
- S3PBT02 does not complete disk-error, crash-recovery, stale-PID process-reuse, force-termination corruption, or full write-after-stop fault injection; those remain S3PBT03.
- No real broker path or live trading readiness is introduced.

